Thank you for this essay. You‚Äôve brought points to the surface which have been overlooked throughout the duration of this case, so i applaud you for that. 

However, i must disagree with some of your vital points. I also have to apologise that my argument will not be as concise and articulate as yours, as i‚Äôm currently sick out of hospital and on heavy painkillers, but i do hope you are able to see where i am coming from. 

Johnny Depp does have a temper. No doubt about it, as you said, he‚Äôs admitted it himself. However having a ‚Äútemper‚Äù doesn‚Äôt automatically equal being a risk to people or being an abuser. 
For reference: my father is slavic (and anyone who knows about slavic parents would have vietnam flashbacks from how they were raised) and he was brought up in a household of physical and mental abuse by the hands of his father (a holocaust survivor as a child, who later went on to fight in 3 other wars) so my grandfather was a damaged man who passed down some unfavourable traits to my father. He had a temper and a rage, that given the right circumstances, could be monstrous. However his temper and rage were moreso a liability to himself, vs those around him. 

The majority of your argument centres around the fact he had a temper, which i completely understand and is a valid point, however it does not directly link to being an abuser. You mentioned him trashing closets and hotel rooms, which are wrong but both Winona and Kate have come out in his defence and have said that that is not the Johnny they knew, and he was never like that in the duration of their relationships. That speaks volumes because we don‚Äôt know the full context behind why he trashed the closets or hotel rooms. Hell, i‚Äôm not defending it but rockstars did it all the time (even w groupies and whatnot present) and that doesn‚Äôt qualify as abuse. This is what i mean when i say having a temper doesn‚Äôt automatically equal violence/abuse, as Johnny would be the one who would have to pay off the debt for his episodes, therefore harming himself (financially) more than he harmed anyone. 

I also find it a little bit of a stretch for you to say he ‚Äúannihilated‚Äù Heard to the public. Johnny was condemned for over a year and rarely spoke about the charges, allowing himself to be publicly shamed, be a victim of character assassination (bc many false truths or lies also came about when this became international news), have his career and livelihood affected, etc etc. It wasn‚Äôt until the recent months he has come back with his own charges, because he‚Äôs spent the last few years gathering all the proof he could from as many sources as possible. He‚Äôs not ‚Äúannihilating‚Äù her, and she‚Äôs no where near as condemned by the media as he was when the story first broke. If anything, it‚Äôs the media creating scandals out of this so it‚Äôs quite unjust to blame Johnny for the way the media sensationalises the story. 

You also mention the coincidental timing of how after this fiasco, suddenly there are a slurry of horrific stories about Amber. You blame it on the machines at work behind the scenes however it seems you‚Äôre dismissing the part that when something goes as viral as these charges, everyone‚Äôs history is dug up and analysed, nomatter who you are. Another reason these stories also came to light is because of the publicity Amber was now receiving; of course now that she is in the spotlight, people who believe her and even those that don‚Äôt, will go looking for things in their past to criminalise them, or decriminalise them. It just so happens that Amber also had a past that wasn‚Äôt completely clean and she, too had been charged with domestic assault before this happened. Sure, her partner at the time has defended her and said it wasn‚Äôt abuse, the police were homophobic etc, but that doesn‚Äôt change the narrative or the facts that she, too has a temper and has been violent in the past. 

You have made many other good points (like when he assaulted a stunt double on set) that there‚Äôs no excusing of. Plus the various reports about his behaviour from multiple sources show he is not in the best frame of mind and most likely suffers from addiction. This is not an excuse but when you look at the situation in a bigger picture, you will realise abuse often isn‚Äôt completely one sided. 
I am by no means trying to fully defend Johnny and paint him as a victim, nor am I condemning Amber. 
If you put the timeline together, it‚Äôs clear that they were BOTH in a toxic relationship that, at times, escalated to physical abuse on BOTH sides. Before this, Johnny was well known to have a temper and trash closets, hotels etc but was never known to be abusive towards his partner. Amber on the other hand, was known for actually committing domestic violence in the past. They‚Äôve both admitted to hurting, hitting, throwing things etc at each party. This does not mean one is the abuser and one is the victim. It means it was a toxic relationship on both sides where both played a part in the severity of the abuse and downfall of the relationship/marriage. 

Personally, my belief is they were both hot heads with tempers. They both knew which buttons to press to get under the other‚Äôs skin and what started out as mild disagreements or fights slowly escalated over the years to spousal abuse against each other. None are innocent. They have both testified to committing abusive acts against the other, so even though you‚Äôve come here with a multitude of facts, that can barely be used as evidence of abuse. I‚Äôm not completely disagreeing as i said, you‚Äôve made some great points and I thank you for taking the time to write these out here, but to completely dismiss Ambers role in this is unjust. She‚Äôs been previously arrested for domestic violence, has testified to hitting, punching, throwing things at him etc under oath. There‚Äôs also a lot we don‚Äôt know because until the trial, the evidence will be withheld from the public. 
All i‚Äôm saying is, i don‚Äôt doubt Johnny probably let his temper (and/or addictions) get the best of him in this relationship. But I also don‚Äôt doubt Amber player just as big of a part in the abuse as Johnny did. To let her off because Johnny has a well documented temper (which we don‚Äôt know the extent of) is just wrong in my eyes. There wasn‚Äôt one victim and one abuser here. It‚Äôs complex with many intricacies and the only way to describe it is a toxic relationship that turned physical and eventually became an abusive relationship on both sides. It‚Äôs also unfair to make a judgement until all information is available to the public; Amber has her side publicly available (albeit, not all of it) but Johnny doesnt have half as much information given to the media. We‚Äôll have to wait for time to do its thing before any fair judgement can be made. 

Also just for reference; i grew up in an abusive/toxic household. The ‚Äúvictim‚Äù was not the victim, but the aggressor who pushed the ‚Äúabuser‚Äù to their limits (both physically, mentally and emotionally) just to cry abuse. They‚Äôre not together anymore, but that person is still claiming to be a victim when anyone who was there could see who the REAL victim was, and it was often the ‚Äúvictim‚Äù that turned things physical as a way to cry abuse. Therefore; the ‚Äúvictim‚Äù in this situation was more guilty than the abuser, but in society it isn‚Äôt seen that way. I‚Äôm studying Psych and in such complex cases, it‚Äôs hardly black and white. In cases like this, it‚Äôs often a result of 2 partners triggering each other and turning things physical. Before making a judgement, remember there is a lot we don‚Äôt know and not everyone is either a ‚Äúvictim‚Äù or ‚Äúabuser‚Äù. In such cases, the lines can be blurred which is why these cases are so difficult to handle, especially in the public eye.
Regardless, thank you for taking the time to write this out and use facts of incidents that have occurred. I do agree to a certain extent however there are things i could not agree with knowing what I know about psychology, toxic relationships, and abuse. It‚Äôs not clear cut so the onus should go on both of them, but again, only time will tell. I hope we can agree to disagree if you do not find my arguments compelling enough (once again i apologise for my writing skills, or lack thereof, but I hope i got my point across!)
